@startuml PrepPanda_Activity_Diagram

skinparam shadowing false
title PrepPanda — Activity Diagrams

|#LightBlue| Admin |
|#LightGreen| System Backend |
|#LightYellow| Database / Storage |
|#LightPink| Student |

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════
' ACTIVITY 1: Chapter Ingestion Pipeline
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════

start
:__**Activity 1: Chapter Ingestion Pipeline**__;

|Admin|
:Upload PDF with chapter metadata
(chapter_number, chapter_title);

|System Backend|
:Validate admin credentials
(Basic HTTP Auth);
if (Authenticated?) then (yes)
else (no)
  :Return 401 Unauthorized;
  stop
endif

:Create chapter row in PostgreSQL;

|Database / Storage|
:INSERT INTO core.chapters
→ chapter_id (UUID);

|System Backend|
:Upload raw PDF to MinIO bucket;

|Database / Storage|
:Store PDF at uploads/chapters/{id}.pdf
→ pdf_url;

|System Backend|
fork
  :Run **NodeParser** (text extraction);
  :Extract text via PyMuPDF (layout mode);
  :Detect NCERT headings (regex patterns);
  :Chunk text at heading boundaries;

  if (Chunk > 550 words?) then (yes)
    :Split at sentence boundaries
    using spaCy (en_core_web_sm);
  else (no)
  endif

  if (Chunk < 20 chars?) then (yes)
    :Discard undersized chunk;
  else (no)
    :Create TextChunk with
    section_path & figure_refs;
  endif

fork again
  :Run **VisualParser** (image extraction);
  :Extract page elements (dict mode);
  :Classify text blocks
  (HEADING / CAPTION / CONTEXT / QUESTION / BODY);
  :Find captions → associate nearest image ABOVE;
  :Render images at 2× upscale via pixmap;

  if (Image blank or too small?) then (yes)
    :Discard image;
  else (no)
    :Group side-by-side images (Y-overlap > 50%);
    :Deduplicate by xref + content hash;
  endif
end fork

:Upload extracted images to MinIO;
:Store image records in core.images;
:Store text chunks in core.chunks;

:Match chunk figure_refs → image captions;
:Create chunk_image_links (M:N);

:Encode all chunks via all-mpnet-base-v2
(batch → ndarray[N × 768]);

|Database / Storage|
:UPDATE core.chunks SET embedding = vector
for each chunk;

|System Backend|
:Return IngestResult
{chunks, images, links};

|Admin|
:View ingestion summary;
stop

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════

|#LightPink| Student |

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════
' ACTIVITY 2: SRS Q&A Pipeline
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════

start
:__**Activity 2: Smart Retrieval Q&A**__;

|Student|
:Enter question in Notes tab
e.g. "What is double fertilisation?";

|System Backend|
:Normalise query
(remove stopwords, lowercase);
:Encode query → 768-dim vector
(all-mpnet-base-v2);

fork
  :Semantic Search via HNSW index
  (cosine similarity, pool = 30);
fork again
  :Keyword Search via GIN index
  (BM25 ts_rank_cd, pool = 30);
end fork

:Min-max normalise each score set;
:Compute hybrid score =
0.7 × semantic + 0.3 × keyword;
:Select top-10 chunks by hybrid score;

:Expand with ±1 neighbour chunks
(context continuity);
:Sort all chunks by position_index
(reading order);
:Fetch linked images from
chunk_image_links;

:Build structured LLM prompt:
  - System prompt (NCERT tutor rules)
  - Context chunks (numbered)
  - Figures with {{IMG:X.X}} tags
  - Student question;

:Call Gemini API
(gemini-3-flash-preview, temp=0.3);

if (LLM response OK?) then (yes)
  :Replace {{IMG:X.X}} placeholders
  with real MinIO image URLs;
  :Return Markdown answer
  with embedded figures;
else (no)
  :Return error message;
endif

|Student|
:View AI-generated answer
rendered as rich Markdown
with inline figures;
stop

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════
' ACTIVITY 3: PYQ Analysis Pipeline
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════

start
:__**Activity 3: PYQ Analysis**__;

|Student|
:Open PYQ Analytics tab;

|System Backend|
:Fetch all PYQ → chunk mappings
from pyq_chunk_map;

:Group mappings by chapter;
:Create raw zones (±2 radius
around each hit position_index);

:Merge overlapping zones
within same chapter
(stack-based interval merge);

:Count distinct PYQ frequency per zone;
:Extract section titles for zones;

if (Zone has non-descriptive title?) then (yes)
  :Call Groq LLaMA to generate
  meaningful zone title from content;
else (no)
endif

:Detect trends per zone:
  - Rising (recent 2 years, high recency)
  - Declining (last asked 3+ years ago)
  - Consistent (spread across years)
  - One-shot (single year only);

:Compute composite_score =
freq × (0.5 + recency_weight);

:Select top-K zones by composite_score;

:Call Gemini API for question prediction:
  - Input: zone content + trend data
  - Output: predicted questions with
    marks, difficulty, confidence,
    reasoning, source traceability;

:Assemble AnalysisReport
{zones, trends, predictions};

|Student|
:View zone cards with frequency badges,
trend arrows, and predicted questions;
stop

@enduml
